      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">Dr. Nandini, working in a rural health post in Maharashtra, India, is actively involved in community health programs. She often collaborates with local self-governing institutions to ensure effective healthcare delivery. During a recent community meeting, a discussion arose about the structure and functions of the Panchayati Raj system at the village level. Which of the following is NOT a part of the Panchayati Raj at the village level?</span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q4278436",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 34843,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        7
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Ans. B. Panchayat Samiti</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><br><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Explanation:</u></strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">The <strong>Panchayati Raj</strong> is a <strong>3-tier</strong> structure of <strong>rural local self-government</strong> in India, <strong>linking</strong> the <strong>village</strong> to the <strong>district.</strong> The three institutions are:</span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><ol style=\"list-style-type:lower-roman;\"><li><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Panchayat</strong> - at the <strong>village level</strong>.</span></p></li><li><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Panchayat Samiti</strong> - at the <strong>block level</strong>; and</span></p></li><li><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Zilla Parishad</strong> - at the <strong>district level.</strong></span></p></li></ol><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Educational Objective:</u></strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>The Panchayati Raj at the village level consists of:</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><ol style=\"list-style-type:lower-roman;\"><li><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">The <strong>Gram Sabha.</strong></span></p></li><li><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">The <strong>Gram Panchayat</strong>; and</span></p></li><li><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">The <strong>Nyaya Panchayat</strong>.</span></p></li></ol><p style=\"text-align:justify;\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align:justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Ref</u>: Park 26<sup>th</sup> ed, pg. 975</strong></span></p>",
